07:01.722 --> 07:05.893
Page: This club is legendary
here in Kiev,

07:05.926 --> 07:11.465
but in 2014 it was the scene
of a violent attack.

07:11.499 --> 07:13.734
A group of right-wing radicals
tried to force their way

07:13.767 --> 07:15.536
into Pomada.

07:15.569 --> 07:18.038
They threw a smoke bomb
and firecrackers into the club,

07:18.071 --> 07:20.741
causing a stampede.

07:20.774 --> 07:25.479
This anti-LGBTQ attack turned
out to be one of many that year.

07:25.513 --> 07:29.049
**

07:30.851 --> 07:35.723
Ukraine is a nation
in transition.

07:35.756 --> 07:39.627
This is the Maidan,
right in the center of Kiev,

07:39.660 --> 07:42.930
where, in 2013, Ukrainians
gathered by the thousands

07:42.963 --> 07:44.798
in protest
of government corruption.

07:53.874 --> 07:56.810
The Ukrainian government
just defaulted on an agreement

07:56.844 --> 07:57.945
with the European Union.

07:57.978 --> 07:59.980
[ All chanting in Ukrainian ]

08:00.013 --> 08:02.916
For many Ukrainians,
E.U. integration held

08:02.950 --> 08:06.654
the promise of political reform
and economic stability.

08:06.687 --> 08:09.757
[ All singing in Ukrainian ]

08:09.790 --> 08:13.661
But for LGBTQ people,
it held the possibility

08:13.694 --> 08:16.664
of steps towards equality
and basic human rights

08:16.697 --> 08:20.300
and a shift
away from Russian influence.

08:20.333 --> 08:22.770
Instead,
the Ukrainian President,

08:22.803 --> 08:24.271
Viktor Yanukovych, opted

08:24.304 --> 08:26.607
for closer relations
with Russian.

08:26.640 --> 08:30.010
Yatsenyuk: This president
betrayed the Ukrainian people.

08:30.043 --> 08:34.014
He sold my country,
and he did it under the auspices

08:34.047 --> 08:35.783
of President Putin.

08:35.816 --> 08:38.819
Page: Eventually,
the protests turned violent,

08:38.852 --> 08:42.155
and clashes erupted
between and demonstrators.

08:42.189 --> 08:44.191
These events have come
to be known

08:44.224 --> 08:46.694
as the Euromaidan Revolution.

08:46.727 --> 08:50.097
[ All chanting in Ukrainian ]
In the end, over 100 protestors

08:50.130 --> 08:52.833
and 18 police officers
were killed

08:52.866 --> 08:58.005
while another 166 protestors
are missing or presumed dead.

09:00.340 --> 09:05.879
Even now,
when I smell this, um, smoke,

09:05.913 --> 09:09.349
it brings just, like, memories
of the -- of the revolution.

09:09.382 --> 09:13.587
Maxim Eristavi is one of
the few openly gay journalists

09:13.621 --> 09:15.155
currently working in Ukraine

09:15.188 --> 09:16.590
and reported
from the front lines

09:16.624 --> 09:18.626
of the revolution.

09:18.659 --> 09:20.794
What does it feel like
when you come back
and just walk around?

09:20.828 --> 09:23.130
All the time,
I find it quite emotional.

09:23.163 --> 09:26.800
It's not normal
when you're in a normal city

09:26.834 --> 09:28.602
living your normal,
urban life,

09:28.636 --> 09:31.204
and then suddenly, you're
in the middle of urban warfare

09:31.238 --> 09:34.708
and with people dropping dead
around you.

09:34.742 --> 09:36.309
So, what is
the current political state

09:36.343 --> 09:38.211
of the country right now?

09:38.245 --> 09:40.247
Personally, I think
the revolution is
still happening.

09:40.280 --> 09:42.082
-Mm-hmm.
-Two years later,

09:42.115 --> 09:46.286
it's not about protests,
violence, and active face,

09:46.319 --> 09:48.255
but it is happening
everywhere --

09:48.288 --> 09:50.290
in minds, in, uh --

09:50.323 --> 09:52.125
in the governmental buildings,
everywhere.

09:52.159 --> 09:53.661
The process is
still there --

09:53.694 --> 09:54.995
this uncertainty,

09:55.028 --> 09:56.964
this desire for change,

09:56.997 --> 09:58.932
a time to change.

09:58.966 --> 10:00.868
Page: We're continuing
our conversation

10:00.901 --> 10:04.371
in a location
away from the square.

10:04.404 --> 10:06.840
Daniel: We understand that you
felt uncomfortable talking

10:06.874 --> 10:08.408
about queer issues
or queer rights

10:08.441 --> 10:09.777
in the Maidan Square.

10:09.810 --> 10:11.178
Why is that?

10:11.211 --> 10:15.649
I think that they politicized
this issue so much

10:15.683 --> 10:20.187
that standing on the Maidan
talking about queer rights

10:20.220 --> 10:21.955
or, you know,
any political issue,

10:21.989 --> 10:24.257
could backfire later,
and you can be accused

10:24.291 --> 10:26.126
either of being
a Kremlin agent

10:26.159 --> 10:27.728
or a traitor.

10:27.761 --> 10:31.264
If I criticize to the country
in any way possible...

10:31.298 --> 10:33.333
-Right.
-...I'm a target...

10:33.366 --> 10:35.068
-Right.
-...for far-rights.

10:35.102 --> 10:37.905
Could you tell us
about the LGBT involvement

10:37.938 --> 10:40.207
in the
Euromaidan Revolution?

10:40.240 --> 10:44.011
LGBT groups, activists,
they decided intentionally

10:44.044 --> 10:47.380
they don't want to bring
social issues into this fight.

10:47.414 --> 10:50.117
A lot of gay people,
a lot of queer people,

10:50.150 --> 10:52.185
they've been there,
and they were fighting

10:52.219 --> 10:54.154
shoulder-to-shoulder
with everyone else,

10:54.187 --> 10:57.390
but it wasn't manifested
in any way.

10:57.424 --> 11:00.861
And I think it was
one of the biggest mistakes

11:00.894 --> 11:05.265
of the queer community here
to, uh, keep it silent.

11:05.298 --> 11:07.400
Now when you talk to people,
they say,

11:07.434 --> 11:09.970
"Well, where have you been
during the revolution?

11:10.003 --> 11:11.839
I didn't see
any gay people fighting

11:11.872 --> 11:14.975
with us there,
so why should we care?"

11:15.008 --> 11:16.476
And I think
that's very tragic.

11:16.509 --> 11:20.280
How does it make you feel
as an out journalist in Ukraine?

11:20.313 --> 11:22.082
I'm trying to do
everything possible

11:22.115 --> 11:25.753
to expose rising, uh, animosity
towards gay people.

11:25.786 --> 11:28.221
But at the same time,
the constant death threats

11:28.255 --> 11:31.324
and then when you look
over your shoulder --

11:31.358 --> 11:34.995
I've been through a lot
of stuff myself personally,

11:35.028 --> 11:37.197
and I know that,
at some point, you know,

11:37.230 --> 11:39.499
you have to stand up
because otherwise,

11:39.532 --> 11:41.835
well, you're gonna
face death anyway.

11:41.869 --> 11:43.837
-Maxim, thank you so much.
-Yeah.

11:43.871 --> 11:45.739
-Thank you for coming.
-Your bravery is, like,

11:45.773 --> 11:48.041
absolutely astounding.
-Oh, it's -- No, it's not.

11:48.075 --> 11:49.743
You don't need to be humble.
It is.

11:49.777 --> 11:50.911
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

11:53.781 --> 11:56.984
As the country regroups
in the wake of the revolution,

11:57.017 --> 12:00.420
where does this leave
the LGBTQ community?

12:00.453 --> 12:04.191
**

12:06.126 --> 12:06.326
**

12:08.428 --> 12:13.333
Page: We are in Kiev,
the capital city of Ukraine.

12:13.366 --> 12:14.467
[ Horn honks ]

12:14.501 --> 12:16.236
[ All chanting in Ukrainian ]

12:16.269 --> 12:17.905
In the years
since the revolution,

12:17.938 --> 12:20.107
there has been
a surge of right-wing activity

12:20.140 --> 12:22.876
in the streets.

12:22.910 --> 12:26.179
These fringe groups
of ultra-right nationalists

12:26.213 --> 12:29.149
have an ideology rooted
in a mistrust of Russian

12:29.182 --> 12:31.418
and the west
and believe in an independent

12:31.451 --> 12:34.321
and socially conservative
Ukraine.

12:34.354 --> 12:37.024
Waging a battle
for Ukraine's morality,

12:37.057 --> 12:39.259
some groups coordinate
violent attacks aimed

12:39.292 --> 12:43.296
at members
of the LGBTQ community.

12:43.330 --> 12:47.400
Local activist Zoryan Kis has
experienced violence

12:47.434 --> 12:49.937
at the hands of such groups.

12:49.970 --> 12:53.340
They want us to --
to be scared.

12:53.373 --> 12:55.075
They want us to hide,
and they told me,

12:55.108 --> 12:58.045
"We will be attacking
every event that you organize

12:58.078 --> 12:59.512
because we don't want you
on the streets."

12:59.546 --> 13:01.281
-Mm.
-"We don't' want you

13:01.314 --> 13:04.584
to demonstrate your sickness,"
or something like that.

13:04.617 --> 13:07.120
So we took part
in an experiment

13:07.154 --> 13:09.990
where me
and my partner, Tymur,

13:10.023 --> 13:12.259
we walked down the city
holding hands,

13:12.292 --> 13:15.863
and there were two secret,
hidden cameras filming

13:15.896 --> 13:17.831
the reaction
of the people.

13:17.865 --> 13:19.299
**

13:19.332 --> 13:24.104
Then we ended up sitting
on a bench at [speaks Ukrainian]

13:24.137 --> 13:26.907
and Tymur was sitting
on my lap.

13:26.940 --> 13:28.508
And then,
within three minutes,

13:28.541 --> 13:31.411
we were approached
by a gang of, um,

13:31.444 --> 13:34.547
far-right teenagers.

13:34.581 --> 13:37.584
They were obviously,
like, neo-Nazi.

13:37.617 --> 13:40.220
They had some tattoos,
and, like,

13:40.253 --> 13:43.156
varying shirts
with various signs.

13:43.190 --> 13:46.894
There were, like,
10 or 12 of them.

13:46.927 --> 13:49.429
They pepper-sprayed us first

13:49.462 --> 13:54.935
and started, uh, kicking
and beating us.

13:54.968 --> 13:59.472
They said we are the shame
of the Ukrainian nation.

13:59.506 --> 14:02.142
**

14:02.175 --> 14:06.179
Page: Some youth groups even go
on so-called "gay safaris"

14:06.213 --> 14:09.316
where they use social media
to lure unsuspecting members

14:09.349 --> 14:13.220
of the community
to attack and shame them.

14:13.253 --> 14:17.057
We've made contact with one of
the most notorious local groups

14:17.090 --> 14:19.526
perpetrating gay safaris
here in Kiev.

14:19.559 --> 14:23.296
**

14:33.340 --> 14:35.575
They're called
Fashion Verdict,

14:35.608 --> 14:39.246
kind of a dark twist
on the phrase "fashion police."

14:39.279 --> 14:41.548
This group allowed
one of our producers

14:41.581 --> 14:43.550
to film for the night.

14:43.583 --> 14:47.320
**

15:24.992 --> 15:29.329
Fashion Verdict was founded
by a name named Nikolay Dulsky.

15:39.539 --> 15:41.674
