that you're a part of

16:14.674 --> 16:17.477
and if you could explain,
um, what you guys do

16:17.510 --> 16:20.747
and maybe how many members
are in your group.

16:32.125 --> 16:35.595
Can you describe more of your
values of these various groups?

17:00.187 --> 17:01.554
[ Sighs ]

17:07.594 --> 17:09.529
I mean, what are your --
maybe your greatest fears

17:09.562 --> 17:13.233
of the things
that negatively impact Ukraine?

17:49.902 --> 17:52.305
Page:
This ideology is spreading.
[ Shouting,
explosion in distance ]

17:52.339 --> 17:54.141
Two weeks before we arrive,

17:54.174 --> 17:57.377
over 200 ultra-right-wing
nationalists laid siege

17:57.410 --> 18:01.881
to an LGBTQ equality festival
in the city of Lviv

18:01.914 --> 18:04.617
350 miles from Kiev.

18:04.651 --> 18:08.388
**
[ Sirens wailing ]

18:09.156 --> 18:12.692
[ Chanting in Ukrainian ]

18:23.403 --> 18:25.605
Page: We're at the headquarters
for Insight,

18:25.638 --> 18:29.842
an organization dedicated
to LGBTQ awareness and advocacy

18:29.876 --> 18:32.345
founded by Olena Shevchenko,

18:32.379 --> 18:35.315
one of the organizers
of the Lviv festival.

18:35.348 --> 18:36.616
What happened there
exactly?

18:36.649 --> 18:38.685
Can you walk us through
your personal account?

18:38.718 --> 18:41.521
So, basically what we did,
we put an advertisement

18:41.554 --> 18:44.524
on social network
that the equality festival

18:44.557 --> 18:46.459
will be held in Lviv.

18:46.493 --> 18:50.363
Yeah, we started, uh,
at 12:00 like we planned,

18:50.397 --> 18:54.901
and in one hour
we calculated more into hundreds

18:54.934 --> 18:57.170
of ultra-rights
around the hotel.

18:57.204 --> 18:59.606
They just surrounded
the hotel.

18:59.639 --> 19:01.808
Mm, and then, when something
like that happens --

19:01.841 --> 19:04.444
Like, I'm just --
I'm wondering how you regroup

19:04.477 --> 19:06.679
'cause it seems like
such a difficult situation

19:06.713 --> 19:08.881
to navigate
when you're just trying

19:08.915 --> 19:11.618
to have a gathering
for equality,

19:11.651 --> 19:13.953
and then you're dealing
with 200 potentially

19:13.986 --> 19:15.888
extremely violent people.

19:15.922 --> 19:20.660
Well, when we came back was
a hugest-ever media attention

19:20.693 --> 19:24.297
from Ukrainian media,
from international, as well.

19:24.331 --> 19:26.466
Um, and it's
a good thing

19:26.499 --> 19:30.803
because, you know, this issue,
uh, became more public.

19:30.837 --> 19:32.339
That's not just,
you know,

19:32.372 --> 19:34.774
an issue of one
minority group anymore.

19:34.807 --> 19:38.578
That's an issue of, uh,
violence in Ukraine.

19:38.611 --> 19:40.680
Could you
maybe speak specifically

19:40.713 --> 19:45.252
to, um, some
of the challenges and issues

19:45.285 --> 19:47.954
lesbian and bisexual women
face in Ukraine?

19:47.987 --> 19:50.790
Of course,
in our patriarchal society,

19:50.823 --> 19:53.393
women's rights is
still something, you know,

19:53.426 --> 19:54.961
not really popular.

19:54.994 --> 19:58.398
First of all, you're women,
and then you are lesbian.

19:58.431 --> 20:00.633
So, basically,
that's a double stigma.

20:00.667 --> 20:02.535
Feminism, like,
that's for radicals.

20:02.569 --> 20:04.237
[ Laughs ]
-Mm-hmm.

20:04.271 --> 20:06.373
But, of course, we are radicals,
and we use this word.

20:06.406 --> 20:09.242
What does that mean for you
when I walk in your office

20:09.276 --> 20:11.444
and I see this image,
which is,

20:11.478 --> 20:14.814
I'm assuming, a target on you
from various organizations

20:14.847 --> 20:16.949
or groups, and what does
that mean for you

20:16.983 --> 20:21.788
and others working here
in that sort of constant fear?

20:21.821 --> 20:24.757
I don't think that we are
working in the fear.
Mm-hmm.

20:24.791 --> 20:27.694
We are, you know,
experienced people

20:27.727 --> 20:30.330
and really
motivated ones.

20:30.363 --> 20:31.764
**

20:31.798 --> 20:34.734
Today, Olena has organized
a flash mob in Kiev

20:34.767 --> 20:37.504
to support Lviv
and to make a public statement

20:37.537 --> 20:39.639
that the community
will not hide in fear.

20:39.672 --> 20:40.773
[ Speaks Ukrainian ]

20:40.807 --> 20:42.842
We need to unite
our efforts.

20:42.875 --> 20:46.313
We need to unite our efforts
to be more visible

20:46.346 --> 20:49.949
and a more vocal movement.

20:49.982 --> 20:53.386
I believe that that's possible
to change something.

20:59.892 --> 21:02.795
I don't plan
to give up.

21:02.829 --> 21:05.732
**

21:07.667 --> 21:08.301
**
Page: We're in Ukraine,

21:09.936 --> 21:11.971
where, according
to a recent study,

21:12.004 --> 21:14.006
63% of Ukrainians surveyed

21:14.040 --> 21:16.509
believe homosexuality is
a mental disease.

21:16.543 --> 21:17.744
[ Horn honks ]

21:17.777 --> 21:20.447
The organization
Gay Alliance is trying

21:20.480 --> 21:24.651
to change that by helping to
educate people on LGBTQ issues.

21:28.821 --> 21:29.922
-Hey!
-Yuri?

21:29.956 --> 21:31.391
-Hey!
-Hey.

21:31.424 --> 21:32.592
-How's it going? I'm Ian.
-Great. I'm Yuri.

21:32.625 --> 21:34.361
Nice to meet you.
-Nice to meet you.

21:34.394 --> 21:35.695
Ellen.
A pleasure to meet you.
Nice to meet you, Ellen.

21:35.728 --> 21:37.530
How's it going?
What's going on?

21:37.564 --> 21:38.865
-Yeah, we saw --
-Um, it's pretty fun.

21:38.898 --> 21:41.868
We are having, like,
kind of informative campaign

21:41.901 --> 21:45.672
just to support
the same-sex partnership.

21:45.705 --> 21:46.873
Mm-hmm.
So, what does this say?

21:46.906 --> 21:48.741
It actually says
that they have right

21:48.775 --> 21:50.810
for a common life together.
-Mm-hmm.

21:50.843 --> 21:53.780
And this says
they have right

21:53.813 --> 21:56.115
to, uh, uh,
grow old together.

21:56.148 --> 21:57.550
Mm.

21:57.584 --> 22:00.086
Page: Today,
Yuri is raising awareness

22:00.119 --> 22:03.456
for a bill
on same-sex civil unions.

22:03.490 --> 22:07.026
**

22:18.004 --> 22:20.540
[ Both laugh ]

23:01.080 --> 23:04.684
[ Fanfare plays ]

23:04.717 --> 23:06.753
Page: The former Soviet Union
has a long history

23:06.786 --> 23:09.656
of using propaganda
to control public opinion.

23:09.689 --> 23:12.659
[ Speaking Russian ]

23:12.692 --> 23:14.160
And so, most recently,

23:14.193 --> 23:16.996
the Russian Parliament
unanimously voted for a bill

23:17.029 --> 23:19.932
criminalizing anything deemed
"gay propaganda,"

23:19.966 --> 23:23.903
which President Vladimir Putin
signed into law in 2013.
[ Camera shutters clicking ]

23:23.936 --> 23:27.674
**

23:29.008 --> 23:32.712
And here in Ukraine, activist
Ruslan Kukharchuk campaigns

23:32.745 --> 23:35.715
in support of a similar law.

23:35.748 --> 23:36.916
-Hi.
-Hello.

23:36.949 --> 23:38.184
Thanks for meeting
with us.

23:38.217 --> 23:39.952
We appreciate you taking
the time today.

23:39.986 --> 23:43.189
Your organization was supporting
and pushing forward a bill

23:43.222 --> 23:46.959
that would make there be
an anti-gay propaganda law,

23:46.993 --> 23:48.828
I believe,
that would lead to a sentence

23:48.861 --> 23:50.062
of maybe five years.

23:50.096 --> 23:52.899
Is that something
you're um, still working

23:52.932 --> 23:54.534
on pushing forward?

24:02.675 --> 24:06.679
That would mean, like, no,
I guess, pride celebrations.

24:06.713 --> 24:09.549
Would that also mean, like,
no gay movies, or --

24:09.582 --> 24:11.718
Say, like,
if an athlete came out

24:11.751 --> 24:13.152
as a gay person --

24:13.185 --> 24:17.724
All of that, I'd imagine,
would become illegal?

24:17.757 --> 24:18.891
Uh...

24:33.740 --> 24:35.174
Right, so, I'm curious,
then, how you feel

24:35.207 --> 24:36.876
about just
freedom of speech

24:36.909 --> 24:39.579
because it seems like you're
for the right to protest

24:39.612 --> 24:44.050
for your organization
but against LGBTQ protest.

25:06.305 --> 25:11.778
**

25:11.811 --> 25:15.882
Page: Despite the best efforts
of Love Against Homosexuality,

25:15.915 --> 25:17.650
we're invited
to one of Ukraine's

25:17.684 --> 25:20.019
first same-sex ceremonies.

25:20.052 --> 25:21.320
-Hi!
-[ Speaks Ukrainian ]

25:21.353 --> 25:22.789
Ellen.

25:22.822 --> 25:25.224
Page: Though unrecognized
by Ukrainian law,

25:25.257 --> 25:28.260
gay-right activists Zoryan
and Tymur are having

25:28.294 --> 25:32.665
a commitment ceremony
at the local LGBTQ center.

25:32.699 --> 25:35.167
If the anti-propaganda law
ever passes,

25:35.201 --> 25:36.769
what we're doing today,

25:36.803 --> 25:39.138
filming a same-sex ceremony
for television,

25:39.171 --> 25:40.840
would be strictly illegal,

25:40.873 --> 25:43.576
and we could all face
up to five years in prison.

25:43.610 --> 25:44.811
Daniel: Well, thanks
for letting us join in.

25:44.844 --> 25:46.846
And can we do anything
to help out?

25:46.879 --> 25:48.815
-Uh...
-Okay, well, you get ready.

25:48.848 --> 25:50.249
Yeah.
Yeah.
We don't -- You know,

25:50.282 --> 25:51.918
we're here
to just hang out.
Okay. [Laughs]

25:51.951 --> 25:53.152
-[ Speaks Ukrainian ]
-No stress.

25:53.185 --> 25:55.221
Okay.
[ Speaks Ukraine ]

25:55.254 --> 25:56.623
[ Laughter ]

25:56.656 --> 26:00.192
[ Organ plays ]

26:26.018 --> 26:29.188
[ Laughter ]

26:36.729 --> 26:39.065
[ Cheers and applause ]

26:41.267 --> 26:42.769
[ Cheers and applause ]

26:42.802 --> 26:47.006
[ All chant in Ukrainian,
laughter ]

26:47.039 --> 26:50.777
**

27:04.323 --> 27:05.157
**
Page:
It's nighttime in Kiev,

27:07.159 --> 27:09.028
and the streets may seem quiet,

27:09.061 --> 27:12.431
but below the surface lives
a small and defiant

27:12.464 --> 27:15.968
underground arts community
that refuses to stay silent.

27:16.002 --> 27:18.237
[ Laughter,
indistinct conversations ]

27:18.270 --> 27:22.074
Misha Koptev is
one such figure in the scene.

27:22.108 --> 27:25.411
Considered by some to be
an outsider because of his art,

27:25.444 --> 27:29.816
his unabashed sense of self has
attracted a cult following.

27:29.849 --> 27:32.719
Daniel: Hey.
[ Chuckles ]

27:32.752 --> 27:35.321
Hi, I'm Ian.

27:35.354 --> 27:37.056
Nice to meet you.

27:40.860 --> 27:43.162
[ Laughs ]
Interpreter: "I had a
dream you were naked
under my blanket tonight."

27:43.195 --> 27:45.397
You had a dream
of me naked?

27:45.431 --> 27:47.433
I think that's called
wishful thinking.

27:49.335 --> 27:50.870
Uh, who are you?

27:50.903 --> 27:52.772
I'm from Viceland.

27:52.805 --> 27:54.306
"Viceland"?

27:54.340 --> 27:56.042
[ Speaking Ukrainian ]
-Yes, you know the channel --

27:56.075 --> 27:57.977
the TV channel?
-[ Speaks Ukrainian ]

27:58.010 --> 28:01.113
I'm here to hang out
with you tonight, so --

28:01.147 --> 28:05.017
I'm in your world,
so take me around.

28:05.051 --> 28:08.788
**

28:15.461 --> 28:17.129
Page:
Misha blurs the boundaries

28:17.163 --> 28:20.299
between performance art
and fashion.

28:20.332 --> 28:22.468
[ Indistinct conversations ]

28:22.501 --> 28:24.703
[ Speaks Ukrainian ]

28:28.007 --> 28:29.475
Daniel: Yes. Okay.

28:32.278 --> 28:33.412
Looking up.

28:37.116 --> 28:39.451
-Oh, thank you.
-[ Speaks Ukrainian ]

28:45.291 --> 28:46.926
-Oh!
-[ Speaks Ukrainian ]

28:46.959 --> 28:49.261
So, wait, wait -- Tell me
what's going on tonight first.

29:00.472 --> 29:04.210
**

29:19.025 --> 29:22.761
[ Indistinct conversations ]

29:23.062 --> 29:25.464
Oh, that's -- Oh!
Oh.

29:25.497 --> 29:28.100
That is your twin.
He's crying?

29:30.269 --> 29:31.470
Why is he crying?

29:38.510 --> 29:40.112
**

29:40.146 --> 29:43.082
Page: Misha gleeful plays
the role of the jester,

29:43.115 --> 29:48.154
but under the surface there's
a lot more to his story.

29:48.187 --> 29:50.857
He is just one
of over 1.5 million

29:50.890 --> 29:52.591
internally displaced Ukrainians

29:52.624 --> 29:55.361
who were forced to relocate
after the Russian invasion

29:55.394 --> 29:57.263
in the Eastern provinces.

30:01.633 --> 30:05.037
After Euromaidan,
the country became destabilized,

30:05.071 --> 30:07.473
and Russia attempted
to annex Eastern Ukraine.

30:07.506 --> 30:08.607
[ Explosion ]

30:08.640 --> 30:10.309
The region broke out into war,

30:10.342 --> 30:15.181
creating a mass exodus of
hundreds of thousands of people.

30:15.214 --> 30:18.317
LGBTQ people like Misha were
among those

30:18.350 --> 30:20.119
who left everything behind,

30:20.152 --> 30:22.889
migrating west toward Kiev.
-Hello?

30:22.922 --> 30:24.924
[ Dog barks in distance ]
Daniel: Wow.

30:24.957 --> 30:26.358
How are you?
We brought you some --

30:26.392 --> 30:28.394
-[ Smooches ]
-...early morning wine.

30:35.467 --> 30:38.004
[ Speaks Ukrainian ]

30:41.573 --> 30:42.942
-The whole thing?
-[ Slurps ]

30:42.975 --> 30:44.276
Interpreter:
[ Speaks Ukrainian ]

30:44.310 --> 30:46.278
[ Coughs ]

30:47.479 --> 30:48.948
[ Speaks Ukrainian ]

30:48.981 --> 30:50.249
"Drink, baby."

30:54.086 --> 30:55.922
Ohh!

31:02.361 --> 31:05.564
Where did --
Where did you get this from?

31:05.597 --> 31:07.499
I'm gonna start controlling
the situation.

31:09.601 --> 31:12.104
Maybe just a little
bite here, huh?

31:12.138 --> 31:15.674
That's so good,
so good.

31:15.707 --> 31:17.543
[ Laughs ]

31:23.149 --> 31:24.316
-Not the --
-No.

31:24.350 --> 31:26.018
No, I don't' think
it's that big.

31:26.052 --> 31:28.087
**

31:28.120 --> 31:29.555
I wanted to ask you
about your hometown

31:29.588 --> 31:32.258
and where you're from
and what it's like there.

32:00.286 --> 32:04.023
**

32:21.607 --> 32:25.244
Page: In a nation torn apart
by war and revolution,

32:25.277 --> 32:28.114
it seems that Misha uses
his renegade art

32:28.147 --> 32:31.083
as a way to make sense
of his world.

32:31.117 --> 32:34.686
But he's only one of countless
LGBTQ people fleeing

32:34.720 --> 32:37.623
the Russian occupation.

32:37.656 --> 32:40.492
We're visiting
the only LGBTQ safe house

32:40.526 --> 32:43.262
for internally displaced people
in Kiev.

32:43.295 --> 32:45.631
-Can we come in?
-Marina and Marina are

32:45.664 --> 32:49.135
a couple who fled their hometown
in Eastern Ukraine.

32:49.168 --> 32:50.669
[ Both speak Ukrainian ]

32:50.702 --> 32:52.571
[ All speak Ukrainian ]

32:52.604 --> 32:55.407
Thank you so much for having us.
We really appreciate it.
Yeah.

32:55.441 --> 32:58.377
So, how did you guys
first meet each other,

32:58.410 --> 33:00.579
and when was the moment
when one of you was, like,

33:00.612 --> 33:03.115
"I'm Marina," and then
you were both like, "Whoa!"

33:03.149 --> 33:05.351
[ Laughter ]

33:16.228 --> 33:18.730
-Wow, that one look.
-Yeah.

33:18.764 --> 33:21.400
So, how long
have you been in Kiev?

33:33.612 --> 33:36.348
Guys, what was it like
on a day-to-day basis

33:36.382 --> 33:39.451
in regards to violence
that was happening?

34:02.641 --> 34:04.676
How did you two make
the decision to leave?

34:30.702 --> 34:33.372
What's the ideal future
for you two?

34:33.405 --> 34:37.143
**

35:01.333 --> 35:05.637
Page: Some LGBTQ Ukrainians have
been displaced by war,

35:05.671 --> 35:09.675
but others can't even leave
if they tried to.

35:09.708 --> 35:11.410
[ Camera beeps, shutter clicks ]
Fritz Von Klein is

35:11.443 --> 35:13.779
a trans man trapped in Ukraine
because the government

35:13.812 --> 35:15.614
will not issue him documentation

35:15.647 --> 35:17.416
that matches
his gender identity.

35:17.449 --> 35:18.550
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

35:18.584 --> 35:21.153
A self-described
artist-activist,

35:21.187 --> 35:24.356
Fritz poses for photographs
as a way of using his body

35:24.390 --> 35:26.925
as an artistic form of protest,

35:26.958 --> 35:29.595
highlighting the difficulties
of simply existing

35:29.628 --> 35:32.664
as a transgender person
in Ukraine.

36:08.700 --> 36:11.237
I'm just wondering
how you feel knowing

36:11.270 --> 36:13.439
that then
the government has control

36:13.472 --> 36:15.741
over who you are
on some level.

36:28.019 --> 36:30.456
You have a kid, yeah,
you have a daughter?

36:30.489 --> 36:33.525
Oh, my God.
It's on rainbow flag.

36:36.928 --> 36:38.264
Aww.

36:40.699 --> 36:44.403
And where do they live?

36:44.436 --> 36:47.339
You're not able
to see her at all?

36:47.373 --> 36:48.507
Wow.

36:50.442 --> 36:52.811
For now,
Fritz lives in Kiev,

36:52.844 --> 36:55.514
which could be considered
a more cosmopolitan city

36:55.547 --> 36:57.416
in the nation.

36:57.449 --> 36:58.650
But what's life like

36:58.684 --> 37:02.588
for LGBTQ people
outside of the city?

37:02.621 --> 37:05.491
Our old friend Vlad,
who performs in Kiev

37:05.524 --> 37:09.461
as his drag persona Guppy Drink,
offered to show us.

37:09.495 --> 37:15.301
Page: We're headed to a town
in rural Ukraine with Vlad,

37:15.334 --> 37:18.504
and, uh, spend some -- spend
some time in his hometown.

37:18.537 --> 37:20.639
**

37:20.672 --> 37:22.674
Page: We're now seven hours
outside of Kiev

37:22.708 --> 37:25.811
in a small town called
Bobrynets.

37:25.844 --> 37:29.348
What was it like being young
and growing up in this town?

37:29.381 --> 37:31.550
Shast: I wasn't able
to be open.

37:31.583 --> 37:34.553
Everyone hates
to be just thinking

37:34.586 --> 37:36.755
about some gay stuff.
-Mm.

37:36.788 --> 37:39.958
But, uh, to be open gay
in this town is like

37:39.991 --> 37:41.660
to be dead.
-Mm.

37:41.693 --> 37:44.663
I heard "faggots," like,
almost every day.

37:44.696 --> 37:45.864
-Mm.
-Hm.

37:45.897 --> 37:47.999
-But it's made me stronger.
-Mm-hmm.

37:52.504 --> 37:53.639
Hm?

38:02.414 --> 38:06.518
And this was my surname
and other bad words --

38:06.552 --> 38:08.787
It's like
"Licking of the dicks."
Mm-hmm.

38:08.820 --> 38:13.792
You can even see
"H", "A, "S," and "T,"

38:13.825 --> 38:16.428
and this was, like,
bad word.

38:16.462 --> 38:19.365
What did you mom say?
How did she feel about it?

38:19.398 --> 38:21.733
We didn't talk
about it, because --
But she saw it, yeah?

38:21.767 --> 38:23.369
I think yes.

38:23.402 --> 38:25.637
And this is not
the first one here, I can say.

38:25.671 --> 38:28.440
There's a few ones was
near my school -- on school.

38:28.474 --> 38:30.008
So...
-Mm-hmm.

38:30.041 --> 38:32.844
...it was
the normal thing.

38:32.878 --> 38:35.080
What does it make
you feel like to see them?

38:35.113 --> 38:38.784
Shast: I don't, like, have
any evil in my heart,

38:38.817 --> 38:42.521
because I understand
that people can do mistakes

38:42.554 --> 38:44.122
and that people can change.
-Mm-hmm.

38:44.155 --> 38:49.361
And I need to show by my example
that to be queer is normal.

38:49.395 --> 38:51.863
Daniel: I'm wondering,
if you didn't have drag,

38:51.897 --> 38:53.665
do you feel like you would have
made it out of this town?

38:53.699 --> 38:56.635
Drag has given me
the opportunity

38:56.668 --> 39:01.106
to say to everyone
that, "I'm here."

39:01.139 --> 39:03.141
I'm queer.
get used to it!

39:03.174 --> 39:04.743
[ Laughter ]

39:04.776 --> 39:07.813
**

39:11.450 --> 39:15.086
Page: We're in Ukraine, where
Kiev Pride is around the corner.

39:15.120 --> 39:17.956
Newlywed Zoryan has organized
a self-defense class

39:17.989 --> 39:21.727
for the LGBTQ community to learn
how to protect themselves.

39:21.760 --> 39:23.429
[ Speaking Ukrainian,
people chanting in Ukrainian ]

39:23.462 --> 39:25.897
Last year he experienced
violence firsthand

39:25.931 --> 39:29.601
during the pride march
when an ultra-right mob attacked

39:29.635 --> 39:32.971
the event with nail bombs,
injuring 19.
[ Explosions ]

39:33.004 --> 39:36.475
And this year,
an ultra-right nationalist group

39:36.508 --> 39:41.680
has promised a "blood bath"
if this event isn't cancelled.

40:18.750 --> 40:21.052
For the last part
of the training session,

40:21.086 --> 40:24.623
Zoryan hints that he will relive
an experience from his past

40:24.656 --> 40:27.158
in order to prepare the class
for Pride.

41:02.861 --> 41:04.730
Oh, shit.

41:06.798 --> 41:11.236
**

41:11.269 --> 41:13.238
Daniel:
He looks in severe pain.

41:13.271 --> 41:18.777
I mean, that shit burns
your eyeballs.

41:18.810 --> 41:22.981
Page:
The fact that he just did that
to be able to show other people

41:23.014 --> 41:24.850
the reality of that experience,

41:24.883 --> 41:27.052
to help members
of your community

41:27.085 --> 41:32.157
feel prepared probably
psychologically more capable

41:32.190 --> 41:34.793
of, you know, going
to these events

41:34.826 --> 41:38.163
or even just walking down
the street with your partner --

41:38.196 --> 41:41.132
It was a pretty
unbelievable thing.

41:41.166 --> 41:44.903
**

41:46.004 --> 41:49.307
It's the day of pride 2016.

41:49.340 --> 41:53.311
The city of Kiev has deployed
5,500 police

41:53.344 --> 41:56.247
and 1,200 members
of the National Guard

41:56.281 --> 41:57.983
to protect the marchers.

42:00.986 --> 42:02.721
Every year since it started,

42:02.754 --> 42:04.890
it's faced serious threats
of violence.

42:04.923 --> 42:08.660
[ Indistinct conversations ]

42:14.232 --> 42:16.968
Man: [ Speaking in Ukrainian
over loudspeaker ]

42:17.002 --> 42:19.004
Page: Despite everything,

42:19.037 --> 42:22.107
the LGBTQ community is
out in full force.

42:41.059 --> 42:44.796
**

42:55.741 --> 42:59.277
[ All chant in Ukrainian ]

43:09.020 --> 43:12.758
[ Cheers and applause ]

43:15.927 --> 43:17.729
For the first time
since it began,

43:17.763 --> 43:20.165
Kiev's pride march ended
peacefully.

43:20.198 --> 43:23.068
[ Cheers ]

43:23.101 --> 43:25.403
While our friends
celebrate today,

43:25.436 --> 43:27.372
tomorrow is a new day

43:27.405 --> 43:31.877
back in the trenches
in the fight for equality.

43:31.910 --> 43:33.311
It's been an honor

43:33.344 --> 43:37.816
to meet members
of Ukraine's LGBTQ community.

43:37.849 --> 43:40.185
They've shown us
that the gentlest souls make

43:40.218 --> 43:42.087
the fiercest warriors,

43:42.120 --> 43:44.322
that real bravery is
moving forward

43:44.355 --> 43:46.725
in the face of uncertainty,

43:46.758 --> 43:49.928
and above all their hard work is
a reminder

43:49.961 --> 43:52.197
that two years after Euromaidan,

43:52.230 --> 43:54.399
their revolution continues.

43:54.432 --> 43:58.269
**
